
Tale-seeker: Someone with a mild interest in folktales, occasionally seeking out stories for enjoyment.
Story-lover: A person who frequently enjoys listening to and reading folktales.
Myth-chaser: Someone who actively seeks out and enjoys various folktales, myths, and legends.
Fable-finder: An individual who enjoys discovering and sharing lesser-known folktales and fables.
Lore-keeper: A person dedicated to preserving and recounting folktales and legends.
Saga-scholar: Someone who studies the historical and cultural significance of folktales in depth.
Legend-smith: A person who not only studies but also creates new folktales, blending traditional and original elements.
Lore-master: An expert in folktales, with extensive knowledge and active involvement in both the study and creation of folktales.